1
00:00:03,204 --> 00:00:04,604
(WHISTLING)

2
00:00:06,364 --> 00:00:08,804
(GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING)

3
00:00:09,564 --> 00:00:10,924
(ALARM BEEPING)

4
00:00:11,004 --> 00:00:12,684
Not now, I'm busy.

5
00:00:14,204 --> 00:00:16,124
All right then, what?

6
00:00:17,044 --> 00:00:18,964
What? What?

7
00:00:22,284 --> 00:00:24,084
01! Get out of my Tardis!

8
00:00:24,164 --> 00:00:26,044
I let down the defences
for one second...

9
00:00:26,124 --> 00:00:27,364
Must speak to the Doctor.

10
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:31,044
I don't care. You're a Graske.
And a Graske is trouble. Out!

11
00:00:32,244 --> 00:00:35,604
But that noise...
Beautiful sound in the air, what is it?

12
00:00:38,964 --> 00:00:43,044
If you must know,
that's the music of the spheres.

13
00:00:43,124 --> 00:00:45,084
Music of the spheres is what?

14
00:00:45,164 --> 00:00:48,684
Well, you got all those planets
revolving around suns,

15
00:00:48,764 --> 00:00:51,564
and all those suns
revolving around in a galaxy,

16
00:00:51,644 --> 00:00:54,844
and all those galaxies
revolving around each other.

17
00:00:54,924 --> 00:00:56,924
If you take the gravity patterns
and feed them

18
00:00:57,004 --> 00:01:01,124
through the Tardis harmonic filter,
that, Mr Graske,

19
00:01:01,204 --> 00:01:03,404
is the sound of the universe.

20
00:01:06,004 --> 00:01:08,524
Universe sounds wonderful.

21
00:01:08,604 --> 00:01:11,124
Yeah. It does, doesn't it?

22
00:01:13,044 --> 00:01:14,204
But you're still not staying.

23
00:01:14,284 --> 00:01:16,004
No, Graske came to warn you.

24
00:01:16,084 --> 00:01:18,084
-About what?
-About that.

25
00:01:19,884 --> 00:01:21,484
Oh, now.

26
00:01:22,804 --> 00:01:26,084
-That looks like a space-portal.
-Told you. Danger.

27
00:01:26,164 --> 00:01:29,404
Nah! It's harmless.
Just a hole in space.

28
00:01:31,284 --> 00:01:33,964
I wonder what's on the other side.

29
00:01:35,644 --> 00:01:37,564
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

30
00:01:38,204 --> 00:01:39,364
Hello.

31
00:01:40,884 --> 00:01:42,564
Where's that, then?

32
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:45,964
Who are all those people?

33
00:01:46,044 --> 00:01:47,244
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

34
00:01:47,324 --> 00:01:48,604
Hold on.

35
00:01:50,084 --> 00:01:53,044
That looks like...
Is that the Albert Hall?

36
00:01:53,924 --> 00:01:56,364
I said, “Is that the Albert Hall?"

37
00:01:56,444 --> 00:01:57,524
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

38
00:01:57,604 --> 00:02:00,324
I said, “Is that the Albert Haiti"

39
00:02:00,404 --> 00:02:01,764
AUDIENCE: Yes!

40
00:02:01,844 --> 00:02:03,524
Oh, great! Hello.

41
00:02:04,484 --> 00:02:06,124
I said, “Hello. "

42
00:02:06,204 --> 00:02:07,444
AUDIENCE: Hello!

43
00:02:07,524 --> 00:02:09,844
No, no, no. Sorry. Sorry.
You'll have to shout.

44
00:02:09,924 --> 00:02:12,284
I said, "Hello!"

45
00:02:12,364 --> 00:02:14,044
AUDIENCE: Hello!

46
00:02:14,124 --> 00:02:16,284
Listen. My name's the Doctor,
I'ma Time lord,

47
00:02:16,364 --> 00:02:19,044
but that is an awful lot of people.

48
00:02:19,124 --> 00:02:21,844
What 're you all doing there? Oh/

49
00:02:21,924 --> 00:02:25,364
Wait a minute. It's the Proms.
Is that the Proms? Are you in the Proms?

50
00:02:25,444 --> 00:02:26,684
AUDIENCE: Yeah!

51
00:02:26,764 --> 00:02:29,524
Oh! I love the Proms.
I was at the very first Proms.

52
00:02:29,604 --> 00:02:31,724
1895, I played the tuba.
I was brilliant.

53
00:02:31,804 --> 00:02:32,844
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

54
00:02:32,924 --> 00:02:36,284
Is that the orchestra down there?
Oh! Wart there/

55
00:02:40,084 --> 00:02:42,604
'Cause funny thing is,

56
00:02:42,684 --> 00:02:45,404
I've just been
composing something myself.

57
00:02:45,484 --> 00:02:47,044
I said to Beethoven,
I said I can rattle off a tune.

58
00:02:47,124 --> 00:02:48,724
He said, "Pardon?"

59
00:02:48,804 --> 00:02:52,924
But I've just been inspired
by the music of the spheres.

60
00:02:53,004 --> 00:02:54,604
I've written my own symphony.

61
00:02:54,684 --> 00:02:58,564
Yeah. And if I can send these pages
through the portal,

62
00:02:58,644 --> 00:03:01,604
then the orchestra can play it.

63
00:03:01,684 --> 00:03:05,764
Brand new piece of music composed by me.

64
00:03:05,844 --> 00:03:10,724
So, are you ready for this, orchestra?
Stand by. Three, two, one...

65
00:03:12,804 --> 00:03:14,404
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

66
00:03:14,484 --> 00:03:16,484
That's it/ That's it/

67
00:03:17,684 --> 00:03:20,164
There you go! Hurry up!

68
00:03:20,244 --> 00:03:23,364
This portal isn't going to stay
open for long, right...

69
00:03:23,444 --> 00:03:27,684
Now, so, if you don't mind,
Mr Conductor.

70
00:03:28,524 --> 00:03:32,724
Stand down.
I'm in charge of this one. Quiet please.

71
00:03:32,804 --> 00:03:35,124
(DOCTOR SHUSHING)

72
00:03:35,204 --> 00:03:38,004
Silence. Settle down. 01, settle down.

73
00:03:38,804 --> 00:03:42,364
So, ladies and gentlemen, children,

74
00:03:42,444 --> 00:03:47,964
this is the world-wide premier
of Ode to the Universe.

75
00:03:49,484 --> 00:03:50,724
And...

76
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:57,284
(ORCHESTRA PLAYING CACOPHONIC MUSIC)

77
00:04:02,004 --> 00:04:03,044
(MUSIC STOPS)

78
00:04:03,124 --> 00:04:05,764
Oh, come on! That was brilliant/

79
00:04:07,364 --> 00:04:10,004
Thank you, I thank you.

80
00:04:10,084 --> 00:04:13,084
No, I thank you.
Really, you're too kind.

81
00:04:13,164 --> 00:04:16,924
You see, Graske,
that's the thing about planet Ear...

82
00:04:17,004 --> 00:04:20,764
What? What? Where's he gone?

83
00:04:21,964 --> 00:04:27,164
Oh, I've lost a Graske.
He must have slipped through the portal

84
00:04:27,244 --> 00:04:28,884
Have you seen him?

85
00:04:28,964 --> 00:04:34,164
Ahh! There he is! Albert Hall,
you've got a Graske on the loose.

86
00:04:35,324 --> 00:04:37,964
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

87
00:04:38,044 --> 00:04:40,444
And he's stolen my water-pistol.

88
00:04:41,244 --> 00:04:44,324
01! Graske, stop it! Behave!

89
00:04:45,404 --> 00:04:47,924
He wasn't trying to warn me. He was
trying to find a shortcut to Earth.

90
00:04:48,004 --> 00:04:50,484
If he escapes, he'll go around
the whole planet causing trouble,

91
00:04:50,564 --> 00:04:55,284
stealing sweets, making smells...
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

92
00:04:55,364 --> 00:04:57,644
I'm just gonna have to reverse
the polarity of the neutron flow

93
00:04:57,724 --> 00:05:00,644
and pull that Graske
back into the Tardis.

94
00:05:01,844 --> 00:05:04,604
-Not fair!
-Oh, I'll give you "not fair”.

95
00:05:04,684 --> 00:05:06,324
I'm gonna reverse
the teleport numbers and send you

96
00:05:06,404 --> 00:05:08,364
all the way to
the other side of the galaxy.

97
00:05:13,644 --> 00:05:15,684
Right.

98
00:05:15,764 --> 00:05:19,204
Well, that was fun and a little bit mad.

99
00:05:19,284 --> 00:05:21,484
But I've got to close this portal
before there's any more trouble.

100
00:05:21,564 --> 00:05:24,604
It's nice to see you all.
But one more thing.

101
00:05:25,564 --> 00:05:27,084
Just remember,

102
00:05:27,164 --> 00:05:29,604
music isn't just orchestras
and pop stars

103
00:05:29,684 --> 00:05:33,364
and special people with albums
and downloads and concerts.

104
00:05:33,444 --> 00:05:34,524
It's you.

105
00:05:34,604 --> 00:05:35,804
(ORCHESTRA PLAYING SLOW SONG)

106
00:05:35,884 --> 00:05:39,124
'Cause the music of the spheres
is all around you.

107
00:05:41,604 --> 00:05:44,244
When you're on your own,
Just close your eyes

108
00:05:44,324 --> 00:05:46,404
and you'll hear it.

109
00:05:46,484 --> 00:05:48,724
Music, inside your head.

110
00:05:49,844 --> 00:05:51,724
'Cause everyone's a musician.

111
00:05:51,804 --> 00:05:54,724
Everyone's got a song inside them.

112
00:05:54,804 --> 00:05:56,844
Every single one of you.

113
00:05:57,724 --> 00:05:58,764
Bye.

